fields: How did you know I was here?
Fate moves in a straight line.
That makes ten thousand heroines conquered. No dating sim can stand against me.
What could be more fun than my class?
Sorry. Please wait until I reach a save point.
Anyone could be a hero and heroine
Why did she have to hit me? My games aren't disturbing anybody.
Seventeen years old, born on June 6th at 11:29:35 AM. My interests?
When I say I'm interested in girls, I don't mean that kind!
Sorry, but could you clean the roof by yourself today?
I mean... Unlike you, I'm totally busy.
Asking a favor, after running into and insulting me?
Don't be ridiculous! I absolutely refuse!
Damn it... That girl makes no sense at all.
She should follow the example of girls in games.
I'm only attracted to girls in games.
Reality is just a crappy game!
Looks like everyone's having trouble with Goth Goth Panic.
That's right. I needn't concern myself with
how absurd and irrational the real world is.
I am the Capturing God... A god of the gaming world!
Okay, on to the next one.
What? This message sounds like a challenge.
Who do you think I am?
Thank you for signing the contract, Kami-sama. Then off we go!
When I ran a wide-range scan, there was a response...
Calm down... Don't succumb to reality... First, I need to save...
I'm a demon sent from Hell, as part of the runaway spirits team.
Oh, and what might this mean?
Oh, right... Today's Thursday? I'll go buy a game.
If you aren't careful, you'll lose your head.
You signed a contract with a demon.
You received the contract, right? From Dokuro-san, the bureau chief?
Contracts in Hell are very strict, so you'll need to be careful.
If you fail to meet the conditions
or break the contract without permission, the collar will activate and remove your head.
That's ridiculous! Get this thing off me!
Once we round up the runaway spirits, it'll be removed!
She's in my class. Takahara Ayumi, I think...
Evil souls that escaped from Hell... Runaway spirits.
They've come to the surface to commit more evil acts.
After all, runaway spirits hide within the heart.
How are you supposed to capture them then?!
That's why we need the assistance of a human "buddy".
In other words, you just have to take its place in her heart.
Then the runaway spirit will be forced to leave.
And the best way to insert yourself into her heart...
is to make her fall in love with you!
You're telling me to conquer a real girl?!
Um, well... A kiss will suffice...
You moron! You've got this totally wrong!
I've never even held hands with a real girl!
My world only requires the girls from games.
That's awful... Just awful, Kami-sama! I didn't realize you were the god of playing video games!
Anyway, now that that's cleared up, get this collar off me.
I'm sorry. I can't do that.
To make up for it, I'll die with you...
We're both bound by the contract...
When the buddy dies, the demon also loses her head.
Aw... And there's a runaway spirit right within my grasp...
I'm making a list of games to replay before I lose my head.
Um, Kami-sama? Aren't you the Capturing God?
Maybe you could do the same thing in real life that you do with the girls in games?
Is that supposed to be a track team?
They couldn't be further from the mark.
None of them have their hair tied up!
Huh? Hair? But that doesn't matter-
Don't be ridiculous! Track team girls are supposed to tie their hair up!
Honestly, don't they realize that the spirit of track
Um, doesn't that only apply to games...
I can't conquer a girl who doesn't put in any effort.
She tied her hair up, Kami-sama!
You'd never see a track team wearing shorts in a game!
I can't do a thing if they aren't wearing bloomers.
I can use my raiment to change how she looks on the outside.
But you're the only one who can change what's inside!
Hey, Otamegane! What's with all the embarrassing signs?
There's a meet coming up... So I'm cheering you on...
So you're getting revenge for making  you clean the roof alone?
Do it again, and I'll kill you!
Are you sure about this, Kami-sama?
In games, your relationship with a girl depends on the number of encounters you have.
For now, I can only water the plant until the flower blooms.
Hey! I told you to stop!
She seems to hate you more now...
In games, hate can quickly turn to love.
Overcoming a fight or an event that makes her hate you will always end up as a plus.
So she doesn't actually hate you right now...
No save function... No backlog... How am I supposed to play this...
Second-years are supposed to wait until we're done running.
But there isn't much time left before the meet...
She thinks she's already on the team.
Aren't you getting a little too cocky?
After running a decent time, all of once?
Excuse me! Please hurry up with my punishment!
You'll find rotten upperclassmen in every world.
Speaking of which, that Otamegane isn't much better.
Now is when he should be up there, cheering you on!
Tomorrow's the day of the meet.
If Ayumi wins, after all the cheering you've done, I'm sure that she'll fall for you.
- Take her to the nurse's office! - Someone go get a teacher! Okay!
Don't you think there was something odd about the hurdles today?
Now that you mention it... The hurdles in that one spot felt closer together than they should have been.
That's the only reason she fell down!
If she doesn't win, we can't...
It appears that we've reached the turning point.
Why did you call me out here?
And what is this? Some kind of sick joke?
I was thinking that you'd eat it. Then you'd do your best in the meet tomorrow.
Have you seen my ankle?! Do you think I can run in the meet?!
You've never run in a real race! Do you even know how fast I was going?!
You might have injured yourself if you were running at full speed.
You always tied your hair up when you ran all-out.
Did you plan to trip from the very beginning?
I just happened to run really well  while the coach was watching, so she put me on the team.
But I haven't been able to run well ever since.
I keep practicing, but I can't improve my time.
It'd be better if I weren't in the meet.
Why... Why can't I run anymore?
Don't worry about it so much.
Just run as fast as you can.
Don't creep me out like that!
Besides, this all happened because of your stupid cheering! Geez!
Will you come to cheer me on tomorrow, at the meet?
Got it! runaway spirit in custody!
A-ha! How do you like that?
I found the mark of love in your eyes that day It was amazing! Hey, Ayumi.
Don't get too cocky, after winning just one race.
That day the magnet in my heart started spinning It was a fluke!
I'll find you no matter what, I won't get lost again Huh? Why did you praise her?
She just congratulated me. We're probably fated for each other
Takahara. Meeting each other out of billions of people
is impossible even on computers Oh, thanks...
I have left this everyday life behind me The interview for the paper, right?
and I have finally graduated Ayumi lost all memory of the capture.
Well, it's probably easier for me this way. Even the blue sky seems fun
Any view with you in it is overflowing with an aura of happiness
Huh? That's right... Where did she go? It won't stop
The fountain in front of the station sprouts a rainbow Hey, Otamegane! What's up with that? Where have you been hiding her?
The time spent waiting for you is precious and irreplaceable Hi, everyone. I'm a new transfer student, Katsuragi Elsie.
I hope that everyone is nice to my brother, Keima, and me!
Hey now... What's that supposed to mean?!
Is Elsie your real name? She looks like a doll!
What's she trying to pull here?
Hey, are you really his little sister?
Yes. I'm one hell of a little sister!
Pfft. You're wasted on that otamegane, Katsuragi.
Just wait... Every girl in the world will be after Onii-sama!
Anyone could be a hero and heroine
I don't know right from left  in the human world yet...
Now, get this guillotine of a collar off my neck!
But you haven't completed the contract.
There are still many runaway spirits in this city.
Am I supposed to capture them all?!
I wanted to do something to help, so I asked Chief Dokuro
If I'm your sister, and we're in the same class, we'll be ready whenever a runaway spirit appears!
Don't tell me that you're going to follow me home.
Don't siblings live together in this world?
Like I said..! You're not my sister!
That's not my point! But I just explained...
No more making concessions to the real world!
I'll never let you into our house!
Oh! How unusual. Keima's with a friend!
Very pleased to meet you. I'm Keima's mother!
Come now, have a seat. If we have plenty of anything, it's chairs.
Oh, right. And what's your name?
Yes! I'm your husband's illegitimate daughter.
This is a letter from my late mother.
My mom used to be in a biker gang.
Keima, forget about your father. He's dead to us!
Don't worry. I'll take good care of you!
Just please let me stay at your house!
No. I can't let you live with us.
You haven't properly established yourself as a little sister.
Let me to teach you something useful.
The basic determining conditions establishing a little sister's identity.
First, blood! As in a blood relationship!
She must be related by blood!
Step-sisters, or others who are "like a sister", may as well be total strangers!
Next, memory! As in shared memories!
Precious family memories forged over time!
But above all, she must care deeply for her older brother.
Yes. This world needs higher standards.
The unqualified should never be classified as little sisters.
You and I share no memories! You've been ruining my life!
Besides... We don't have the same blood running through our veins!
N-Now we have the same blood running through our veins.
Please! I want to hunt down runaway spirits!
So in other words, I just have to be a good little sister. Yep!
Mother's gone to talk with someone called a lawyer.
I already know what's going to happen!
You're going to serve me really bad food!
It's twice as good as the fish from this world.
It looks fifty-thousand times more disgusting!
To make this, I cooked my heart out for you.
It's actually pretty good. Isn't it?
I just now noticed... This room looks really clean.
Along with the other rooms. And the store!
I'd say you did more than just tidy up... The house looks almost new.
I was on cleaning duty for three hundred years, after all!
Yep! I've had this broom for 298 years!
Inside, there's magic to help me clean.
One sweep, on the lowest setting, will do the trick.
I'm sorry. It was on the highest setting...
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
It must have been that pasta!
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
Damn it! I don't even know where to start!
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
She barely resembles a demon, but the second she does something, she's like an incarnation of Beelzebub.
I have to get rid of her.
And she couldn't ever be my little sister!
Since I'm the reason for your upset stomach, I thought I could at least scrub your back for you...
No way! It doesn't matter what you try! I'll never accept you as a little sister!
Stop triggering these made-up little sister events!
I'm not making anything up. I really am a little sister.
She excels at everything she does. A true demon among demons...
But... I was completely the opposite.
Stuck on cleaning duty every day...
So when I was selected for the runaway spirit team, I was so happy, I could have died.
I mean... I finally had the chance to do a demon's work!
I live in the gaming world. I won't let myself get carried away by the moment.
I operate on logic and reason.
And my logic and reason tell me
that I should accept you as my little sister.
Really? Unfortunately, that's the best solution.
I want nothing to do with you.
But there isn't any point in kicking you out.
I can't get rid of you anyway, while this collar's around my neck.
So there's only one logical solution...
Capture those runaway spirits and complete our contract.
Don't touch me! I'm doing this for my own benefit!
And you can use this opportunity to improve your record. That might earn you some praise from your sister.
Nope. I used soap, too, to make sure it was super-clean!
This story focuses on a human, who is completely absorbed in a single task.
The artist, Ryoshu, was said to be so skilled, he could suck the soul out of his model.
Consequently, his art was surrounded by dark rumors.
To my Onii-sama and Kami-sama, I, Elsie, am so happy that we can live together now.
On that note, can we talk during lunch today?
P.S. Please forget about what happened in the bath. It was embarrassing.
Why are you reading it out loud?!
Why not? You wanted him to know, right?
So, what happened in the bath?
What happened in the bath? What happened in the bath?! What happened in the bath?!? What happened in the bath?!?!
It doesn't matter how many there are!
I'll catch every single one and fulfill this contract!
What's wrong? Do you feel unwell?
There's more than enough for all you hungry kids!
The food in our cafeteria's expensive, so everyone buys sandwiches from that stand.
Everyone's favorite omelet soba sandwich is on a first-come, first-served basis!
Oh... It's a fried-noodle sandwich that's wrapped in egg.
They use an original sauce that's really good, or so I've been told.
This is the runaway spirit signal. It must be nearby.
So it's responding to someone in that crowd?
No. It's coming from a different direction...
Here's your omelet soba sandwich! That'll be 100 yen.
Out of 10,000? I can't take that. Don't you have any change?
Sorry, but I've never carried change in my life.
Give me as many omelet soba sandwiches as this will buy.
Enough of your squawking, commoners. If you don't like it, become rich like me.
And the one with the runaway spirit is...
Aoyama Mio, sixteen years old. She's in high-school class 2-A.
Daughter of the owner of Aoyama Central Industries. Her birthday is January 2nd.
It'll take a lot of effort to tame a girl with a will that strong.
What are you talking about? She looks relatively easy to handle.
Let me teach you something useful.
They may make a show of being tough, but on the inside, they're very delicate and uncommonly pure.
Once you've broken through the armor, she'll be as soft as putty.
How can you be so certain, without even speaking to her?
Cat-like eyes! Light-colored hair! A high forehead! Twin pigtails!
Those mean there's a 99% chance she fits the mold!
I've seen three hundred of those. In your games?
But of course. It'd be 100% if she were also short.
Wow, look at the soles on those shoes... Kami-sama!
Ah, I thought you already ran off.
From the moment I met you.
I-I'm supposed to work as your buddy, so... Um... Well...
How was that love confession? Huh?
For some reason, it didn't feel right.
Maybe I should try the one from Compress Love...
I was trying out a love confession from a game.
It's actually easier to catch aggressive girls by surprise.
So you confess your love at the very beginning, rather than letting them dictate the pace. We'll be throwing the opening punch.
I'll run down the list. You tell me which ones leave a strong impression.
I've had my eye on you all along.
It makes me blush, even though  I know you're joking.
I'm serious. You're all I can think about!
I'm going by the script! Read the damned list!
I'm in love with you. Would you go out with me?
I give up, I give up! I give up!
You must be tired, after such a long day.
Why did she turn you down? I don't get it.
She didn't even bat an eyelash.
I was expecting her to turn me down, but not like this...
Did I make a mistake in my assumptions?
Yes! I'm using my raiment to track them.
In the real world, it's pretty hard to find out where someone lives.
Normally, an icon would indicate the girl's location.
My lady, I can no longer condone this nonsense!
Please stop pretending to be rich!
I am the daughter of the owner of Aoyama Central Industries.
I refuse to alter my lifestyle.
Anyone could be a hero and heroine
You're no longer the daughter of a rich family.
to hold my head up, as a member of the Aoyama family.
Your mother works hard to make ends meet!
What do we do with all of this?
That wasn't my fault. I only had a ten thousand yen bill.
That was your allowance for the upcoming four months!
You must learn to carry change.
It's impossible for you to eat a hundred sandwiches, and they'll spoil before you know it. Then what will you do for lunch?
If there is no bread, then I'll eat sweets.
That's it. I'm going on leave!
Where are you going, Morita? You're my chauffeur!
I'm the director's chauffeur, not yours!
You're the commoner who just confessed his love to me!
A-Are you here to confess again? Know your place, vulgar one!
I thought that Mio-sama was rich, but she's actually poor.
He saw me. What should I do?
Did she think you were spying on her?
We're off to a bad start again.
No. This is a big step forward.
Let me teach you something useful.
No one at Mai Academy knows that Mio is poor.
In other words, only she and I know.
The two of us share a secret now. This can become a strong bond.
Even if it's a secret you heard by spying on her?
Didn't I already explain this? A bad impression can become a good impression.
But that's only in your games...
Have I ever mentioned the real world before?
When humans head into battle, do they prefer using an unfamiliar weapon?
I will continue to follow the gaming world's tenets! As I fight real world battles!
I don't get it, but that's so samurai, Kami-sama!
Allow me to offer transport to school.
When I heard that your chauffeur had left, I rushed right over.
The commoner who's been confessing his love and spying? Why do you keep popping up?
Please take a seat on the back.
We must hurry, or we'll be late. Come!
How could I possibly ride your bike? I'd rather walk!
You won't be able to walk too well in those shoes. Please get on the bicycle.
I refuse to ride on that cheap piece of junk!
I was impressed by your dedication to maintaining a high-society image.
I suppose I have no choice. My legs hurt, so I can't walk.
I'll be here after school, to take you home...
This conquest will take a lot of stamina...
I really don't understand rich people.
Have a... nice... day... Have a... nice... day... Have a... nice... day...
Katsuragi, pull yourself together. Enough lying around. Get back to pedaling.
Today's carriage is too big for a gamer's legs!
Doesn't she realize that needless escalation will only break the game balance?!
Then I'll use a special charm to make you feel better.
Yes. I'm sure that once I hit you with this, you'll be up and running again!
Why are you carrying a riding crop around?!
I wasn't expecting her to physically attack me!
I'm going home. I shouldn't be wasting time on a commoner.
Given that I come from Hell, it might seem odd for me to say, but I believe that Mio's actions are wrong.
She's poor, but she continues to act rich, for the sake of appearances.
And she acts so proud of being a rich family's daughter, but she didn't burn any incense for her father.
You should pay your respects to the dead.
Hard to believe, coming from a demon.
But it appears that she's a good person at heart.
That's the only logical conclusion, according to the route I anticipate.
This character type tends to act selfishly, before finally warming up.
Picking her up and dropping her off.
And inappropriate behavior. I've triggered enough events.
Something else is holding her back...
I apologize for the delay, my lady.
Is the dress to your liking?
I had to select it myself.
I-I never told you to bring me to this party!
It must be suffocating to spend all your time in that old apartment.
I was thinking that you needed to experience real high-class events occasionally.
Th-That's not what I was talking about!
This is the backyard! You stupid chauffeur!
Well, I'm not very confident in my dancing ability.
I was hoping you might give me a few pointers first.
Are you planning to join the party? You must be joking.
This event is for the rich and famous only.
I've participated a number of times.
Oh! So you've been here before.
But of course. I came here with Papa many...
Fine. You can hold a party here by yourself.
Though there won't be any guests, attendants, or chefs.
Hey! What's with the flashy dress?
You should be wearing something that won't draw attention! You're a maid!
Why do I have to be a maid? I want to wear a dress!
We aren't here to enjoy ourselves!
Don't you want me to teach you to dance? Come over here.
I don't have time to waste on the masses, so we'll do this in one minute.
What are you doing? Give me your hand.
You don't know anything? Hold my hand!
What is it? Never mind. It's nothing... Never mind. It's nothing...
H-Holding hands isn't a big deal. It's a natural part of dancing!
Up, up, down, down, L, R, L...
Still, this seems like something from a storybook.
This is typical of high-society life.
A world that has nothing to do with me.
I've danced with Papa so many times.
Aren't you the daughter of the Aoyamas'?
Mio-san. What are you doing here?
If you're here, you should come inside.
I didn't want to come. Then why are you here?
Well, in any case, I was sorry to hear about Director Aoyama.
Mio-sama, I've heard that you're living with your mother in an apartment?
Hey, you shouldn't be so rude.
I'm sure that you're going through a difficult period, so please help yourself to the food inside.
I wouldn't have expected her to show her face.
She's probably just here for the food.
What's the point in clinging to this lifestyle?
Didn't you say that you would help me?!
I'm sure that your father is satisfied.
You lived the way your father wanted, to preserve his memory.
That's why you pretended to be rich and didn't burn incense for your father.
But you should live your own life now.
Papa... Papa lives on in my heart.
If I live the way he wanted, he'll never die!
You never smile. But just once, you looked alive! Like you were having fun!
I understand that it's important to respect your father's wishes. But!
I want to see you smile more.
You pretended to help me, but it was all a trick!
Ever since you showed up, Papa's been getting smaller...
At this rate, Papa will... Papa will really die...
Nevertheless, I want to live in your heart!
If you don't want me, you can return to that world!
Decide how you will live your life!
Thanks to you, we've already captured two runaway spirits!
I'd like to buy an omelet soba sandwich. Are these coins enough?
I've never used change before. I can't tell which is which.
That should be enough for two. I see.
Mio's willing to use change now!
But she still acts the same.
It's too bad that she lost her memory.
You could have gotten to know each other more.
She's better off forgetting about her father and me.
This way, she can live her own life.
I'll take two omelet soba sandwiches!
You've been holding on to those for me?
Say... Will you look at my picture?
Just believe in myself and my dream Anyone could be a hero and heroine
There once was a game that could not be conquered...
A game that drew many challengers and crushed them...
There's no one left to look at my picture...
I keep telling you not to eat and play at the same time!
El-chan, could you help make sure that Keima doesn't walk into any cars.
Kami-nii-sama, you need to be careful, or you'll get hit by a car.
I think that they just seem to be more clever as they obey our command.
Do you think you can do whatever you want if you answer correctly, huh?!
Houses sprawling across the land, in an extensive web.
Do you still consider me a God?
Normally, you're brimming with confidence. What happened today?
Still, it must be really hard, for you to have trouble.
Why don't you have a look at this game before you say anything?
First, we have the heroine of this game, Asuka Sora.
And here we have a scene where she shows her picture to the player.
Hmm? Huh? She's asking the same question again.
There's a bug that causes this scene to loop!
Normally, the game would move on to the next screen, but a programming error keeps returning the player to the previous scene.
In hindsight, there were signs when I bought this game...
A tearjerker for you?! The release was pushed back twenty-three times!
Spend more time debugging instead of making merchandise!
The first two-disc masterpiece on the PFP? The second disc was just a huge patch, you morons!
So the game was released, but then this bug came up...
It's no use... The patch doesn't fix it...
One bug removed, and another one pops up.
Another game to shelve... I'm done.
Everyone gave up on the game.
Still, I thought that I could solve it.
But I can't do anything about a bug...
Get a hold of yourself, Kami-sama!
I-If the game is broken, it's not your fault.
You may be the Capturing God, but you can't do the impossible.
Who said anything about this being impossible? Huh?
No game can stand against me. Thus I am a God!
Victory will be mine! My pride is on the line.
You need to write down every choice I make.
We can't be sure that the loop is caused by the choice immediately before it.
It's possible that the loop may be avoided by following a different pattern of choices.
So we're looking for a path that doesn't lead to a dead end.
Okay, we're going to try every possible pattern. Game start!
Two out of three times, this game won't start up.
This is the first choice you make in the game.
I chose not to go to the cafeteria earlier, so I'll go this time.
Do we have to go through every one of these?
We don't know which choice will change destiny.
How long is this going to take?
You can't save in this game.
If you save, your PFP stops working.
So we'll have to start over from the beginning every time we fail.
Who's the person collecting runaway spirits for you?
You're going to help me, right? Yes...
According to the developers, it's part of the atmosphere.
Now there's an old man on the screen... Delete your leftover characters!
Cafeteria, omelet-rice, like, win the mini-game, art room, and yes triggers the loop.
Kami-sama... I can't take any more of this...
It's going to be the same result every time.
We haven't tried all of the choices yet. The chances aren't zero.
Does it really matter if there's a game you can't beat?
Why isn't he tired yet? He's been playing that game for so long...
I wish he'd be as dedicated when it came to capturing runaway spirits...
I brought you something to drink.
I'm going to eat lunch now.
I always have udon for lunch. What are you going to have?
I'll have, uh... The lunch lady's special.
Why am I playing dodgeball? Why add a pointless mini-game?!
I'm going to eat lunch now.
I always have udon for lunch. What are you going to have?
You've been holding on to those for me?
Say... Will you look at my picture?
I always have udon for lunch. What are you going to have?
I'll have the lunch lady's... I mean, the fresh school special.
I'm going to eat lunch now.
I'm going to eat lunch now.
I always have udon for lunch. What are you going to have?
You always say that reality is just a crappy game, so why do you care so much about a bad game?
Who'd look at Sora's picture, then?
This clearly is a crappy game. But that isn't Sora's fault.
There's no such thing as a bad heroine. There are only bad games.
Heroines are always waiting for someone to save them!
I can't abandon her just because the game doesn't work!
Oh, I know! We aren't making any progress.
So we should complain to the company that made this game!
That company went out of business last month.
The people who trapped Sora in this loop are gone.
Say... Will you look at my picture?
Yes. If that's what you want.
I broke out of the loop.
I did it! I did it...
I can see it... I can see the ending!
I knew that more issues would crop up.
However, I will not be defeated by mere bugs.
For I am the God of the Gaming World! Let's do this!
What?! Let's go home already! Kami-sama!
One hundred hours of gaming a day!
Naru Hall is mine! Here I go!
Anyone could be a hero and heroine
Here it is! The NNS Best New Artist award goes to...
You did it! You did it, Kanon!
The stage is yours! Here's "All 4 You!"
Kanon won Best New Artist, Kami-nii-sama.
The most popular idol right now! Look!
